 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uniden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Niden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 319<br> <font color=#333333>(5/21/02 6:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=887.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Soloing Xalgoz</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> This is very possible to do as early as 51, and very easy to do after 55.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I've shamelessly bastardized these maps from <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com">EQAtlas</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  Sorry, Muse. :]  Travel route is shown in blue.  Red squares indicate static spawns -- some of them are approximations from memory, although the first pillar and the church are accurate.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Route to Five Towers</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jaddesign.com/download/kaesora1.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
The first thing you need to do is get down to the Five Towers area.  The safest way to do this is to fight down, as the strathbone healers see through invisibility, as do the undead.  Summon an earth pet at the zone in, buff it, and tell it to sit there.  Levitate yourself, and then run forward and drop into the shaft.  Do not go all the way to the bottom, take the corridor in front of you halfway down the shaft.  Take a few steps in, and summon companion.  There is one spider that spawns immediately to your right, usually a strathbone healer.  Kill it, and then proceed forward to the 'Broken Floor' room (Area 7 on the map).  <br>
<br>
Drop down if the room is clear, and summon companion.  The tunnel forward and to your left will lead up to the zone out.  The tunnel behind you and to your right will lead down toward the church area.  Tell your pet to follow you, and proceed down that tunnel, killing any mobs you encounter.  Your pet should easily be able to solo any mobs you encounter in this area, but you should nuke if one of the healers adds.  You'll come to a crossroads with a path to the right and a tunnel forward -- proceed forward into the Five Towers top area.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Kaesora 'Five Towers' Top</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jaddesign.com/download/kaesora2.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Getting through this area is easy, just stick to the left wall and kill any roamers you run into.  The mobs in the first 'pillar' area should not aggro if you hug the wall.  When a tunnel opens in the wall to your left, take it, and you'll emerge into Five Towers bottom.  Tell your pet to guard at the bottom of the tunnel, because you have to clear some mobs to get into the church.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Kaesora 'Five Towers' Bottom</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jaddesign.com/download/kaesora3.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
These mobs are slightly higher level.  Depending on your level, some will be blue/light blue.  If you are 55+, most will be green and you should easily be able to single pull everything.  The danger here is that a group of these mobs can kill you unless you are careful, and the pathing/aggro here are not perfect.<br>
<br>
Directly in front of you is a 'pillar' that contains four mobs.  Pull these one or two at a time back to your pet.  Be careful not to get right up against the wall of the church, as mobs will sometimes aggro.  Move up and pull the mobs between the other pillar and the church, and then kill the two spawns at the entrance of the church.  You should be able to single pull these without a problem using malosi, or scars if you're higher level.<br>
<br>
The top floor of the church contains four spawns: One in the middle of the room, one to either side of the altar, and Xalgoz/Xalgoz's PH behind the altar.  Pull them in that order, and then bring your pet in and park him behind the altar.  Once you're inside the church, you only need to clear the spawns on the top floor, and the two entrance guards so you have some room to maneuver.  The mobs on this floor are on an approximately 20 minute cycle, and Xalgoz's placeholder is on about a 30 minute cycle.  You'll want to try to space the pops in the room so you have about a minute to kill each one, and you'll want to have them all dead before Xalgoz's placeholder spawns.  You'll want to sit on the left side of the room (the side opposite the hole in the floor) to avoid aggro from the stairs.  Every once in a while, one or two of the mobs below will aggro on your pet while he's fighting -- it's not really a problem, just be prepared for it.<br>
<br>
